        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 4:39PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 439 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Dierks, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dierks, Lockesburg, Gillham, Center Point, Lebanon, Provo, Silver
Ridge, Geneva and Burg.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
